{"type":"message","id":"1f31f2c2","parentId":"b3af558f","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:27:29.148Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me summarize the complete situation:\n\n**Running Services:**\n1. ✅ `openclaw-gateway` (v2026.4.15) on port 18789\n2. ✅ `openclaw-v8` (scorer) on port 3103\n3. ✅ `openclaw-listener` on port 3106 - but MISCONFIGURED (points to 3102 which doesn't exist)\n4. ❌ `openclaw-context-api` - trying to use same port 3106, crashing in restart loop\n\n**Cron Jobs:**\n1. ✅ `wiki-learn` - error (auth problem with API key)\n\n\n2. ✅ `Memory Dreaming Promotion` - OK\n3. ✅ `memory-maintain` - OK\n4. ✅ `memory-keeper` - OK\n5. ✅ `summary-pruner` - next run scheduled\n\n**Port 3102 Issues:**\nThe listener is configured to connect to the gateway at `ws://127.0.0.1:3102`, but the actual gateway is running on 18789 instead. There's nothing listening on 3102 at all, which means the listener can't establish its WebSocket connection.\n\n**Core System Architecture:**\nThe gateway on 18789 has the v8 router built in, which handles the scoring engine and scene classification internally rather than as separate services on 3102. The hooks and三层记忆 are functioning as expected.\n\n**Authentication Failures:**\nThe wiki-learn cron job is throwing 401 errors because the API secret key is missing from the request headers.\n\n**Port 3102 Problem:**\nThe openclaw-listener is configured to use port 3102 for both its WebSocket connection to the gateway and for intent/score API calls, but the gateway isn't actually listening on 3102—it runs on 18789 instead. This mismatch means the listener can't reach the gateway at all.\n\n**Actual Setup:**\nThe listener seems to be an older component that predates the current architecture where gateway functionality was consolidated into the main process. Now the question is whether the listener should be reconfigured to connect to the gateway at ws://127.0.0.1:18789, or if it should be disabled entirely since the gateway already handles everything it used to do.\n\n**Verifying Service Functionality:**\nI need to confirm whether the v8 scorer and scene classifier on 3103 and 3105 are actually working as expected, and check if the hooks are triggering properly.","thinkingSignature":"d817d169c45c17df3d0f18249d52d38b96816336a349d3ead916b4d53b812915"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6qsvhkf6jcqy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test the actual working services end-to-end\necho \"=== Testing 3103 (v8 Scorer) ===\" \ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3103/api/score -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写一个复杂的Python多线程爬虫\"}' 2>&1\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Testing 3105 (Scene Classifier) ===\"\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3105/classify -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写一个复杂的Python多线程爬虫\"}' 2>&1\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Checking ephemeral recent ===\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/ 2>/dev/null | tail -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46488,"output":696,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68822,"cost":{"input":0.0139464,"output":0.0008351999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016079879999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776428832055,"responseId":"06315a1f7b60b8298589f6d917b09edb"}}
