{"type":"message","id":"e0f8dc74","parentId":"7ce53a71","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:38:47.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the information I need:\n\n1. **minimax provider**: `https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic` with `MiniMax-M2.7` model. Auth is via `authHeader: true`.\n2. **codingplan provider**: `https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1` with `minimax-m2.5` model. API key is `J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE`.\n\nBut wait - looking at the auth-profiles.json, it only has `volcengine-plan:default` - not the Minimax API key! The actual Minimax API key might be stored elsewhere.\n\n\nI'm noticing a discrepancy: the `auth-profiles.json` file doesn't contain the Minimax key, yet the openclaw.json shows a Minimax provider configuration. This suggests the API key is either stored in a `.env` file or embedded directly in the config itself - the same issue I encountered earlier with the D:\\coam\\.openclaw setup where the `.env` had a placeholder rather than the actual key.\n\nGiven that my earlier test successfully called the Minimax M2.7 API, the real credentials must be accessible somehow, even if they're not visible in these configuration files. The most practical solution would be to route the LLM call through the existing proxy at `http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score` if it supports chat completion requests, or alternatively make a direct call to the Minimax API endpoint using the credentials from the config.","thinkingSignature":"53f5fb2218f4904e429e3d7da777a381a5105021b50d112ecba41299a2b2a574"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rvx9m9pf3qik_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/v8/src/scoring/adapter.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65389,"output":379,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87406,"cost":{"input":0.0196167,"output":0.0004548,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021369779999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776429517476,"responseId":"06315ccb22415f9bc8f171bc8fcb88d8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1b6c8e1","parentId":"e0f8dc74","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:38:48.060Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rvx9m9pf3qik_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * 适配层：直接使用 v7 评分模块 scoring.js\n */\nconst path = require('path');\n\n// v7 模块的实际路径\nconst V7_BASE = '/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/task-orchestrator-v7';\n\nlet v7Scorer = null;\nlet v7Loaded = false;\n\ntry {\n  const scoring = require(path.join(V7_BASE, 'scoring.js'));\n  v7Scorer = scoring.default || scoring.taskScorerV7 || scoring;\n  v7Loaded = true;\n  console.log('v7 scoring module loaded successfully');\n} catch (err) {\n  console.warn('v7 scoring module not found, using built-in scorer:', err.message);\n}\n\n/**\n * 评分结果转换 - v7 转 v8 格式\n */\nfunction convertV7Result(v7Result) {\n  if (!v7Result) {\n    return builtInScore('');\n  }\n\n  const total = v7Result.total || 0;\n  \n  // 根据分数映射到策略\n  let strategy = 'DIRECT';\n  let timeout = 30;\n  \n  if (total > 12) {\n    strategy = 'MEGA_TASK';\n    timeout = 7200;\n  } else if (total > 8) {\n    strategy = 'PARALLEL_SHARDS';\n    timeout = 160;\n  } else if (total > 5) {\n    strategy = 'SPAWN_SUBAGENT';\n    timeout = 120;\n  } else if (total > 2) {\n    strategy = 'STEP_ARCHIVE';\n    timeout = 60;\n  }\n\n  return {\n    score: total,\n    factors: v7Result,\n    recommendedStrategy: strategy,\n    timeout\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * 统一的评分接口\n */\nasync function scoreTask(prompt, context = {}) {\n  if (v7Loaded && v7Scorer && v7Scorer.score) {\n    try {\n      const v7Result = v7Scorer.score(prompt);\n      return convertV7Result(v7Result);\n    } catch (e) {\n      console.warn('v7 scoring failed, using built-in:', e.message);\n    }\n  }\n  \n  return builtInScore(prompt, context);\n}\n\n/**\n * 内置简易评分器\n */\nfunction builtInScore(prompt, context = {}) {\n  let score = 0;\n  const factors = {\n    logicComplexity: 1, risk: 1, estimatedDuration: 1,\n    resourceCost: 1, uncertainty: 1, dependencyComplexity: 1\n  };\n  \n  const lower = prompt.toLowerCase();\n  if (lower.includes('refactor')) { factors.logicComplexity = 3; score += 3; }\n  if (lower.includes('delete') || lower.includes('rm ') || lower.includes('rm:')) { factors.risk = 3; score += 3; }\n  if (lower.includes('build') || lower.includes('compile')) { factors.estimatedDuration = 3; score += 3; }\n  if (lower.includes('test')) { factors.resourceCost = 2; score += 2; }\n  if (lower.includes('api') || lower.includes('http')) { factors.uncertainty = 2; score += 2; }\n  if (lower.includes('monorepo') || lower.includes('workspace')) { factors.dependencyComplexity = 3; score += 3; }\n  \n  if (prompt.length > 500) { score += 2; }\n  else if (prompt.length > 200) { score += 1; }\n\n  let strategy = 'DIRECT', timeout = 30;\n  if (score > 80) { strategy = 'MEGA_TASK'; timeout = 7200; }\n  else if (score > 60) { strategy = 'PARALLEL_SHARDS'; timeout = 160; }\n  else if (score > 40) { strategy = 'SPAWN_SUBAGENT'; timeout = 120; }\n  else if (score > 20) { strategy = 'STEP_ARCHIVE'; timeout = 60; }\n \n  return { score, factors, recommendedStrategy: strategy, timeout };\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { scoreTask };\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776429527999}}
{"type":"message","id":"14d92f02","parentId":"a1b6c8e1","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:39:01.154Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The 3103 service is just a scoring service, not a chat completion service. It doesn't handle LLM generation for the session-summary hook.\n\nNow I need to decide the best approach for the session-summary hook to call LLM:\n\n1. **Option A**: Direct API call to Minimax API (`https://api.minimaxi.com/v1/messages`) using the API key from... somewhere\n2. **Option B**: Use the codingplan provider (`https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1/chat/completions`)\n3. **Option C**: Use a local LLM via Ollama (if available on the network)\n\n\n4. **Option D**: Call the Gateway's WebSocket API to send a message and get a response\n\nThe real issue is that the Minimax API key isn't in auth-profiles.json, and while it's embedded in openclaw.json for the minimax provider, that config only defines the baseUrl and auth settings—it doesn't actually contain the secret key itself. The API key must be stored somewhere else, possibly in a .env file or retrieved from the environment.\n\nFor the session-summary hook, I could either call the Minimax API directly if I can find the key, or route through the Gateway's WebSocket API instead. Let me check if there's a .env file that might have the key.","thinkingSignature":"eca828fac0ee0ffe96cb4ce8c9d385e880a8d7101333f98a416a916aa385beea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_li51xkpfjaji_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/.env 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/claude.env 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# Check if the gateway exposes an HTTP API for chat completions\ncurl -s http://localhost:18789/v1/models 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# Check if there's an LLM proxy or tunnel configured\nls ~/.openclaw/proxy/clients/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":66660,"output":404,