{"type":"message","id":"b53a14fd","parentId":"54b9f508","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:45:44.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The 401 errors started at `1776427363078` and `1776425710616` - these are the two most recent runs, and they both failed with 401. The previous runs (all before that) succeeded. And importantly, the 401 error runs used **MiniMax-M2.7** model and **minimax** provider.\n\nLooking at the successful runs, most used **MiniMax-M2.7** (from the `minimax` provider) and some used **deepseek-chat** or **qwen2.5:14b**. But the two most recent failures used `MiniMax-M2.7` with `minimax` provider.\n\n\nThe error message about the missing Authorization header is coming from MiniMax's API endpoint at `api.minimaxi.com` - that's where the authentication is failing. So the issue is that the cron jobs are trying to call MiniMax directly, but they're not properly authenticating with the API key.\n\nLooking at the provider configuration, the minimax provider uses the Anthropic messages API endpoint and has `authHeader` enabled, but the actual API key (`sk-cp-...`) isn't being sent in the request. The key is configured in `auth-profiles.json` but the cron job is hitting the API without proper authentication headers. So the issue is that MiniMax-M2.7 is failing with a 401 on that endpoint, while deepseek-chat and qwen2.5:14b worked fine. The root cause is likely either the API key being invalid, the minimax provider's auth header configuration being misaligned with the API requirements, or the API endpoint being incorrect. I should note that the session-summary handler was correctly updated to use the codingplan API instead of direct MiniMax. For the wiki-learn 401 issue, the fix depends on what the cron job is actually using—the successful runs used deepseek-chat, so I need to identify whether the cron job switched to MiniMax-M2.7 more recently or if there's a configuration mismatch with the minimax provider auth.","thinkingSignature":"4df63e699bddedc0fe0ff74e27f069c5ce1e779ad6be831346d252ee0171a506"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r4d22ubukwjn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 openclaw.json 中 minimax provider 的配置\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nproviders = d.get('models',{}).get('providers',{})\nminimax = providers.get('minimax',{})\nprint(json.dumps(minimax, indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# 测试 minimax API 直接调用\ncurl -s -X POST \"https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic/v1/messages\" \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: sk-cp-TVuvlmq_fUfdvSwhbwPgAxgFoBCtPc1acKznw8MU2HeWtkWozK3ruBwFLNV2YKdlaYI5BCuiqQnWaI_kB6rmyrYw37SYXtIR1th4i71CR82WvLFT2kKZ_Ls\" \\\n  -H \"anthropic-version: 2023-06-01\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"max_tokens\":10,\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"hi\"}]}' 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90193,"output":726,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112557,"cost":{"input":0.0270579,"output":0.0008711999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029227379999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776429924024,"responseId":"06315e6041d5a5425bff496a42d43f5a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c47181a2","parentId":"b53a14fd","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:45:46.909Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r4d22ubukwjn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic\",\n  \"models\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"name\": \"MiniMax M2.7\",\n      \"reasoning\": true,\n      \"input\": [\n        \"text\",\n        \"image\"\n      ],\n      \"cost\": {\n        \"input\": 0.3,\n        \"output\": 1.2,\n        \"cacheRead\": 0.06,\n        \"cacheWrite\": 0.375\n      },\n      \"contextWindow\": 204800,\n      \"maxTokens\": 131072\n    }\n  ],\n  \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n  \"authHeader\": true\n}\n---\n{\"id\":\"06315e77006828b26d1479054278123a\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"content\":[{\"thinking\":\"The user just says \\\"hi\\\". This\",\"signature\":\"4bfbe2016b4e6d6b809c19808e5870de5b584ac49b3678cd416a0d9c38b5002c\",\"type\":\"thinking\"}],\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":42,\"output_tokens\":10},\"stop_reason\":\"max_tokens\",\"base_resp\":{\"status_code\":0,\"status_msg\":\"\"}}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2280,"aggregated":"{\n  \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic\",\n  \"models\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"name\": \"MiniMax M2.7\",\n      \"reasoning\": true,\n      \"input\": [\n        \"text\",\n        \"image\"\n      ],\n      \"cost\": {\n        \"input\": 0.3,\n        \"output\": 1.2,\n        \"cacheRead\": 0.06,\n        \"cacheWrite\": 0.375\n      },\n      \"contextWindow\": 204800,\n      \"maxTokens\": 131072\n    }\n  ],\n  \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n  \"authHeader\": true\n}\n---\n{\"id\":\"06315e77006828b26d1479054278123a\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"content\":[{\"thinking\":\"The user just says \\\"hi\\\". This\",\"signature\":\"4bfbe2016b4e6d6b809c19808e5870de5b584ac49b3678cd416a0d9c38b5002c\",\"type\":\"thinking\"}],\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":42,\"output_tokens\":10},\"stop_reason\":\"max_tokens\",\"base_resp\":{\"status_code\":0,\"status_msg\":\"\"}}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776429946842}}
{"type":"message","id":"44240c93","parentId":"c47181a2","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:45:58.208Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The minimax API works fine when called directly with the correct endpoint and Authorization header. So the problem is not with the API key or endpoint.\n\nThe 401 error from the cron runs says \"Please carry the API secret key in the 'Authorization' field of the request header\". This means the Gateway's LLM call is NOT sending the API key in the Authorization header.\n\nLooking at the provider config:\n- `authHeader: true` - this should make the gateway send the key as `Authorization: Bearer <key>`\n- But the 401 says the key is NOT being sent\n\nThe API key in `auth-profiles.json` under `minimax:cn` is what the Gateway uses when the agent specifies `minimax` provider. \n\nI think the real issue is that `auth-profiles.json` has `volcengine-plan` but the cron is using `minimax:cn` which is configured in `openclaw.json` under `auth.profiles`. These might not be properly linked, so when the Gateway tries to authenticate with the minimax provider, it's not actually picking up the right credentials.","thinkingSignature":"e66c08bf828352e71079f7c2b5d081f5cdb081e5bfac0cf5f878f198432fdeb4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_akskr941fzvj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 auth profiles 映射\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nauth = d.get('auth',{})\nprofiles = auth.get('profiles',{})\nprint(json.dumps(profiles, indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# 检查 gateway 的 token\ncat ~/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\ngw = d.get('gateway',{})\nprint('mode:', gw.get('mode'))\nprint('auth:', json.dumps(gw.get('auth',{}), indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91219,"output":403,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113260,"cost":{"input":0.0273657,"output":0.0004836,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02914758}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776429946913,"responseId":"06315e7a815a58b42f0743951edec9a6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e45c520b","parentId":"44240c93","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:45:58.733Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_akskr941fzvj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"openai:default\": {\n    \"provider\": \"openai\",\n    \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n  },\n  \"deepseek:default\": {\n    \"provider\": \"deepseek\",\n    \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n  },\n  \"minimax:cn\": {\n    \"provider\": \"minimax\",\n    \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n  }\n}\n---\nmode: local\nauth: {\n  \"mode\": \"token\",\n  \"token\": \"__OPENCLAW_REDACTED__\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":267,"aggregated":"{\n  \"openai:default\": {\n    \"provider\": \"openai\",\n    \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n  },\n  \"deepseek:default\": {\n    \"provider\": \"deepseek\",\n    \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n  },\n  \"minimax:cn\": {\n    \"provider\": \"minimax\",\n    \"mode\": \"api_key\"\n  }\n}\n---\nmode: local\nauth: {\n  \"mode\": \"token\",\n  \"token\": \"__OPENCLAW_REDACTED__\"\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776429958646}}
{"type":"message","id":"53344fd5","parentId":"e45c520b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:46:16.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the auth profiles, but the key is not shown. Let me check the actual content of auth-profiles.json vs what the provider needs. The minimax provider config says `authHeader: true` which means it wants the key in the Authorization header. The auth-profiles.json has the key under `minimax:cn.key`.\n\nWait, but the actual API endpoint for minimax is `https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic/v1/messages` and the config has `baseUrl: https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic`. \n\nThe minimax provider config in openclaw.json has `api: anthropic-messages` which means it uses the Anthropic message format. The Gateway should send the request to `{baseUrl}/v1/messages` with `Authorization: Bearer {key}`.\n \nSo the 401 error about missing the Authorization field suggests the Gateway isn't actually sending the API key in the header even though `authHeader: true` is set. The cron runs that failed were using the minimax provider directly, which means the key was configured but not being attached to the request properly.\n\nThe cron job runs an isolated agent session that calls the LLM, and the 401 is coming from the LLM API call itself, not from wiki-learn script. The real problem is that the Gateway was restarted at 20:09 and the last successful cron run was around 20:04, but then two consecutive failures happened around 20:28 and 20:36 — all using MiniMax-M2.7. This timing suggests the restart might have broken something in how the API key is being passed to the LLM provider. The 401 errors started at 20:28, just 18 minutes after the gateway restart at 20:09, which suggests the restart might have corrupted something. Since the MiniMax API itself works fine when called directly, the issue is likely with how the gateway is configured to use it. The gateway has the correct API URL and auth settings, but the key stored in `auth-profiles.json` might have been altered during the restart or other changes today.","thinkingSignature":"d21984fc8b032fd91e1f01a540f5cc3e3df9a75a384dff9770fd274012690557"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y2cc1rq5yjr7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91746,"output":485,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113869,"cost":{"input":0.027523799999999998,"output":0.0005819999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029404079999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776429958736,"responseId":"06315e864b10bb2910e808b133346ccd"}}
