cking memory sub-agent. Defaults to off for speed.\"\n    },\n    \"promptOverride\": {\n      \"label\": \"Prompt Override\",\n      \"help\": \"Advanced: replace the default Active Memory sub-agent instructions. Conversation context is still appended.\"\n    },\n    \"promptAppend\": {\n      \"label\": \"Prompt Append\",\n      \"help\": \"Advanced: append extra operator instructions after the default Active Memory sub-agent instructions.\"\n    },\n    \"maxSummaryChars\": {\n      \"label\": \"Max Summary Characters\",\n      \"help\": \"Maximum total characters allowed in the active-memory summary.\"\n    },\n    \"logging\": {\n      \"label\": \"Enable Logging\",\n      \"help\": \"Emit active memory timing and result logs.\"\n    },\n    \"persistTranscripts\": {\n      \"label\": \"Persist Transcripts\",\n      \"help\": \"Keep blocking memory sub-agent session transcripts on disk in a separate plugin-owned directory.\"\n    },\n    \"transcriptDir\": {\n      \"label\": \"Transcript Directory\",\n      \"help\": \"Relative directory under the agent sessions folder used when transcript persistence is enabled.\"\n    },\n    \"qmd.searchMode\": {\n      \"label\": \"QMD Search Mode\",\n      \"help\": \"Override the QMD search mode used by the blocking memory sub-agent. Defaults to fast lexical search; use inherit to match the main memory backend setting.\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n===\n{\n  \"id\": \"lobster\",\n  \"name\": \"Lobster\",\n  \"description\": \"Typed workflow tool with resumable approvals.\",\n  \"configSchema\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"additionalProperties\": false,\n    \"properties\": {}\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776430597012}}
{"type":"message","id":"3001a21f","parentId":"c5e49bfe","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:56:54.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the config schemas:\n\n**Active Memory**: Simple - just need to set `enabled: true` in `plugins.entries.active-memory`. It has a lot of config options but only `enabled: true` is required.\n\n**Lobster**: Empty config schema - no config needed, just need to enable.\n\nLet me also check what the current config looks like for these plugins, and then make the changes.\n\nFor Active Memory:\n- Config path: `plugins.entries.active-memory.enabled = true`\n\nFor Lobster:\n- Config path: `plugins.entries.lobster.enabled = true`\n\nLet me also check the Context Engine. The document mentioned it as \"Context Engine\" but the plugin list showed \"lossless-claw\" - let me check if that's the right one.\n\n\nBefore I proceed, I should verify whether these plugins can actually be enabled through config.patch, since some plugins require installation via `openclaw plugins install` rather than just configuration changes. Let me start by modifying the configs to enable both Active Memory and Lobster, then restart the gateway to see if they activate properly.\n\nI need to understand the config structure first—whether these plugins are already registered in the system or if I need to install them. From what I can see in the plugin list, Active Memory and Lobster both show as \"disabled,\" which means they exist but just need to be enabled through configuration rather than installed.\n\nMy plan is to patch the config to enable both plugins, restart the gateway, and verify they're working. For Context Engine, I should check if it requires installation or just configuration.","thinkingSignature":"20dc34270fefabd077334c126eaadeb552f93e07b45bf1062a38d21669e6d3fa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d0u1z6fa1l3e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check current plugin config entries\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nplugins = d.get('plugins',{}).get('entries',{})\nfor k in ['active-memory','lobster','lossless-claw','context-engine']:\n    if k in plugins:\n        print(f'{k}: {json.dumps(plugins[k])}')\n    else:\n        print(f'{k}: NOT IN CONFIG')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42959,"output":449,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65046,"cost":{"input":0.0128877,"output":0.0005388,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014724780000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776430597078,"responseId":"0631610472d5f571432461fd8ce770f6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b372424c","parentId":"3001a21f","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:56:54.508Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d0u1z6fa1l3e_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"active-memory: NOT IN CONFIG\nlobster: NOT IN CONFIG\nlossless-claw: NOT IN CONFIG\ncontext-engine: NOT IN CONFIG"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":232,"aggregated":"active-memory: NOT IN CONFIG\nlobster: NOT IN CONFIG\nlossless-claw: NOT IN CONFIG\ncontext-engine: NOT IN CONFIG","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776430614405}}
{"type":"message","id":"b08eb5d3","parentId":"b372424c","timestamp":"2026-04-17T12:57:06.500Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So none of these plugins are in the config! I need to add them with `enabled: true`. Let me use config.patch to add these entries.For Active Memory, the minimal config is:\n```json\n{\"plugins\": {\"entries\": {\"active-memory\": {\"enabled\": true}}}}\n```\n\nFor Lobster:\n```json\n{\"plugins\": {\"entries\": {\"lobster\": {\"enabled\": true}}}}\n```For both at once:\n```json\n{\"plugins\": {\"entries\": {\"active-memory\": {\"enabled\": true}, \"lobster\": {\"enabled\": true}}}}\n```\n\nBut wait - the plugin list showed them as \"disabled\" not \"not in config\". If they're not in config, how are they \"disabled\"? It might be that when a plugin is in the system but not in config, it defaults to disabled. Adding it with `enabled: true` should enable it.\n\nLet me try the config patch. I need to use the openclaw config patch command or the tool. Let me use exec to run the config patch via openclaw CLI.\n\n\nNow I'll execute the config patches for both plugins.","thinkingSignature":"de8092b594fd3a3a8e163152fff5003d2421fc80404b3e19cae92c650ba4bb14"},{"type":"text","text":"<thinking>\n### 1. 需求拆解\nActive Memory 和 Lobster 都不在配置文件中。需要添加条目并设为 enabled。\n\n### 2. 方案推演\n- config.patch 工具可以热修改配置，无需重启即可生效\n- 同时 patch 两个插件，一次写入\n\n### 3. 风险评估\n- 风险等级：MEDIUM（配置修改，可回滚）\n- 回滚方案：再次 patch 将 enabled 改回 false\n\n### 4. 最终决策\n用 config.patch 同时启用 active-memory 和 lobster。\n</thinking>\n\n`[!WARNING]` 配置修改，MEDIUM 风险，但可热生效无需重启，立即回滚。\n\n执行第1步——同时启用 Active Memory + Lobster：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9wj7zn4r0z8h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs config patch --json '{\"plugins\":{\"entries\":{\"active-memory\":{\"enabled\":true},\"lobster\":{\"enabled\":true}}}}' 2>&1 | tail -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43454,"output":454,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65546,"cost":{"input":0.0130362,"output":0.0005448,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01487928}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776430614510,"responseId":"06316114bbe8dcd951e1335ef0fa1a0e"}}
