{"type":"message","id":"e44411b4","parentId":"1077b0a4","timestamp":"2026-04-17T13:02:54.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Edge CDP is not running. This is a Windows-only setup. Let me check if the browser plugin can work without Edge (perhaps with a headless browser or other means).\n\nActually, looking at the document again, browser automation is specifically tied to Windows Edge because of China's network restrictions on Chromium. Without Edge running on Windows, the browser automation can't work.\n\nThe browser plugin is \"loaded\" but has no configured Edge connection. This is an environmental dependency I can't fix from WSL alone - it requires:\n1. Windows side running Edge with `--remote-debugging-port=9222`\n2. netsh portproxy set up on Windows\n\nLet me check if there's an alternative approach - maybe a local Chromium can be used instead.Let me check if there's any chromium/chrome available in WSL.","thinkingSignature":"47042f9b7618b8fb9c9083bc064a3a3f736b42a82a6ed61586ca8ad7be13b1e4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dj0zcq92214p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which chromium-browser chromium google-chrome 2>/dev/null || echo \"No chromium in WSL\"\nwhich playwright 2>/dev/null || echo \"No playwright CLI\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45681,"output":219,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67538,"cost":{"input":0.013704299999999999,"output":0.0002628,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01526538}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776430967573,"responseId":"06316276bc49837d18e87fcb8af84f37"}}
