{"type":"message","id":"26f4798e","parentId":"1dcedbf2","timestamp":"2026-04-17T13:04:37.011Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Chromium is running with CDP on port 9222. Now I should configure OpenClaw's browser plugin to use this. But the browser plugin config schema was empty. Let me check if there's a way to configure the browser CDP URL through the gateway config.\n\nActually, the browser plugin might automatically connect to a local CDP URL. Let me check if the gateway needs to be configured to use the browser.\n\nWait - the document says browser automation is for Windows Edge. The agent-browser tool in WSL seems to be for local automation. The OpenClaw browser plugin (which is loaded) might need the Edge CDP on Windows.\n\nLet me think about what \"跑通\" means for browser automation:\n\n\nI need to clarify whether I'm aiming for the Windows Edge setup described in the docs or a local Chromium solution that works in WSL. The agent-browser tool is available and functional with Chromium, so that's a viable path, but the OpenClaw browser plugin's CDP configuration is unclear. Let me focus on getting the local Chromium working first, then address the Windows Edge integration if needed.","thinkingSignature":"02fe6956149c5b4503b8ae222034baa943a5cd4fbbaf6bbfbc23edc6547e5b20"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3no326b3s6de_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try agent-browser with local chromium\nagent-browser --cdp 9222 open https://www.baidu.com 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48641,"output":274,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70553,"cost":{"input":0.014592299999999999,"output":0.00032879999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01621938}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776431065469,"responseId":"063162d8a05e3ea409f5f22a89ba8c44"}}
