{"type":"message","id":"043e555d","parentId":"4e05e11f","timestamp":"2026-04-17T13:05:21.423Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 115 TaskFlows are \"task_mirrored\" - they are mirrored from external coding agents (looking at the goals, they're all about 番茄小说 app development). The Controller is \"n/a\" meaning they're not controlled by an OpenClaw internal controller.\n\nLooking at the document, \"Task Flow Managed\" likely refers to OpenClaw's own internal task orchestration through the TaskOrchestrator. These mirrored flows are externally created by ACP/Codex sessions.\n\nThe distinction is:\n- `task_mirrored`: External agent tasks tracked by OpenClaw (from Codex/Claude Code sessions spawned via ACP)\n\n\n- `task_managed`: OpenClaw's own internal task orchestration\n\nSince these are mirrored from external agents and the system is functioning as designed - OpenClaw is tracking them - I should stop here. Looking at what's actually been accomplished, Active Memory and Lobster are now enabled with working CDP, Context Engine is built-in, and Task Flow mirrors external agents as intended. The 115 mirrored flows are a feature, not a bug.\n\nNow I need to verify the remaining checklist items -羊毛系统 has 21 skills installed, session-summary hook is operational, and wiki-learn is running. The main remaining issue is ensuring Chromium persists as a background service so browser automation continues working after restarts.","thinkingSignature":"2b0a55bcfbe70764971a9fcc24e2cbb2e759ba76a870bf243bae5f72c080b54b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wp6k7wdylowq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Create systemd service for chromium to persist\ncat > ~/.config/systemd/user/chromium-cdp.service << 'EOF'\n[Unit]\nDescription=Chromium CDP Browser for OpenClaw\nAfter=network.target\n\n[Service]\nType=simple\nExecStart=/usr/bin/chromium-browser --headless --disable-gpu --remote-debugging-port=9222 --no-sandbox --disable-dev-shm-usage\nRestart=always\nRestartSec=5\nEnvironment=DISPLAY=:0\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=default.target\nEOF\n\nsystemctl --user daemon-reload 2>&1 | tail -2\nsystemctl --user enable chromium-cdp.service 2>&1 | tail -2\nsystemctl --user start chromium-cdp.service 2>&1 | tail -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50102,"output":455,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72195,"cost":{"input":0.0150306,"output":0.0005459999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01687488}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776431107274,"responseId":"063163016dd5bcd2f787e48b748cee53"}}
