{"type":"message","id":"4e7320c2","parentId":"f49b438a","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:20:50.609Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants a rigorous, strict review and inspection of the current system. I need to be critical and thorough - not just checking if things are running, but actually examining if they are working correctly and up to the standards described in the v2026.4.14 documentation.\n\nLet me think about what to check:\n\n1. **Functional verification** - not just \"is it loaded\" but \"does it actually work\"\n2. **Integration testing** - do components talk to each other correctly\n3. **Security review** - are there any risks\n4. **Performance** - any resource issues\n\n\n5. **Configuration validation** - are the settings actually correct and aligned with the documented standards\n\nI'll run through a systematic diagnostic approach, starting with the most critical issues I spotted earlier - like the session-summary hook that was fixed but never actually validated, Active Memory's default behavior of running on every message which could be inefficient, and Lobster's disabled state which needs verification. I should also double-check the listener's intent and score field routing to make sure those are configured properly, and trace through the memory pipeline to confirm it's working end-to-end.\n\nNow I'm noticing the context-api service is still running despite being marked as disabled, which is odd. More concerning is that ephemeral data stopped being written after 21:57 but we have no new sessions since then - that's actually expected since we've been in the same session, so ephemeral gets written per-turn within a session. Let me verify that ephemeral writing is still happening for the current conversation. I should also check the actual gateway logs for any warnings or errors, test whether the v8 scoring and classification services are responding correctly, verify the browser automation can actually execute tasks through the CDP connection, and run through the cron jobs to ensure they're completing successfully.\n\nFor the v8 scoring and classification endpoints, I'm checking both the old v1 format on port 3102 and the current /api/score format on 3103 to ensure they're both responding correctly.","thinkingSignature":"55892c13462d3a427692b20ff1a8bf10c33d2e488fbb102a842e4b61b73d6069"},{"type":"text","text":"\n<thinking>\n### 1. 需求拆解\n用户要求\"犀利、严格\"的评审——不是表面检查，而是深入验证每个组件是否真正工作、配置是否正确、有无隐患。\n\n### 2. 方案推演\n**严格检查清单**：\n1. **v8 Scorer (3103)** — 实际发请求验证响应\n2. **v8 Classifier (3105)** — 实际发请求验证响应\n3. **Listener 配置** — 读取 config.json 验证 gateway.url 和 api.intent 是否正确\n4. **Active Memory** — 检查配置默认值（每个消息都触发会有效能问题）\n5. **Browser CDP** — 实际执行一个 browser 操作\n6. **session-summary hook** — 检查 handler.js 是否真正能读 session 文件\n7. **ephemeral** — 验证当前 session 有在写入\n8. **auth-profiles** — 验证 minimax:cn key 是否还在\n9. **Gateway 日志** — 检查 WARN/ERROR\n10. **3100端口** — 这个端口一直不明\n\n### 3. 自我质疑\n- 我之前说 listener 配置已修复，但从未实际验证过它能否连接 gateway\n- Active Memory 如果默认对每个消息都阻塞，会有效能问题\n- 3100 端口从来不明——这可能是第三方服务\n\n### 4. 最终决策\n逐项执行严格测试，不停留在\"服务存在\"，要验证\"服务可用\"。\n</thinking>\n\n开始严格审查，逐项验证：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p44490lh11ru_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 1. v8 Scorer 实际测试 ===\"\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3103/api/score \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"text\":\"帮我写一个Python脚本\"}' 2>&1\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 2. v8 Classifier 实际测试 ===\"\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3105/classify \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"text\":\"测试消息\"}' 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":859,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":81696,"totalTokens":82613,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0010308,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.030636,"total":0.0316842}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776435622914,"responseId":"063174a6bbc0e91035374a63a8acbf67"}}
