way connection closed\"}\n{\"level\":\"info\",\"time\":\"2026-04-17T14:21:07.895Z\",\"pid\":149465,\"hostname\":\"ai\",\"delay\":1000,\"attempt\":1,\"msg\":\"Scheduling reconnect\"}\n{\"level\":\"info\",\"time\":\"2026-04-17T14:21:08.896Z\",\"pid\":149465,\"hostname\":\"ai\",\"url\":\"ws://127.0.0.1:18789?token=***\",\"msg\":\"Connecting to Gateway\"}\n{\"level\":\"info\",\"time\":\"2026-04-17T14:21:08.898Z\",\"pid\":149465,\"hostname\":\"ai\",\"msg\":\"WebSocket connected\"}\n{\"level\":\"info\",\"time\":\"2026-04-17T14:21:08.898Z\",\"pid\":149465,\"hostname\":\"ai\",\"msg\":\"Gateway connected, replaying queued messages\"}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776435671013}}
{"type":"message","id":"0450d996","parentId":"58c06b01","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:21:28.236Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found critical issues:\n\n1. **Listener WebSocket is unstable** - it's connecting, then closing every ~10 seconds with code 1000 (normal closure), then reconnecting. This means the listener is in a constant reconnect loop. This is the root cause issue - the listener isn't staying connected.\n\n2. **Browser CDP** - `url` is not a valid command for agent-browser. I need to use a different command to check.\n\nLet me investigate why the listener keeps getting disconnected. The log shows:\n- Connected\n- Gateway connected, replaying queued messages\n- 10 seconds later: WebSocket closed (code 1000, reason \"\")\n- Immediately reconnects\n\nThis looks like the gateway is closing the connection after some time. \n\nThe listener's heartbeat might be failing, or the gateway could be cutting idle connections. The listener is configured to send heartbeats every 30 seconds, but if it's being disconnected after only 10 seconds of inactivity, that points to the gateway having a much shorter idle timeout setting.\n\nLooking at the intent configuration, it's pointing to the scoring endpoint which might not handle intent requests properly. More critically, the listener has queuing enabled but I need to verify whether the gateway is actually configured to receive webhook events from it in the first place.\n\nThe listener's repeated \"Gateway connected, replaying queued messages\" pattern suggests it's reconnecting and attempting to resend messages it never successfully delivered. The 10-second closure with code 1000 indicates the gateway is actively closing the connection rather than timing out passively. I should check if the listener is misconfigured to close its own connection, or if the gateway has a max connection lifetime setting that's prematurely terminating it. Also, the listener's `reply.enabled: false` is appropriate since it shouldn't auto-reply to messages.","thinkingSignature":"5e60ccba3c80486fe0a5abd29e05e8af06209d0ec0e601aede18cc382032e787"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_19gllpz7immk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== 9. 3100 端口是什么 ===\"\nlsof -i :3100 2>/dev/null | head -5\nss -tlnp | grep 3100\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 10. Ephemeral 当前session写入测试 ===\"\nwc -l ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/2026-04-17-13.jsonl 2>/dev/null\necho \"当前时间: $(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 11. Active Memory hooks 检查 ===\"\nls ~/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":63115,"output":555,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85308,"cost":{"input":0.0189345,"output":0.0006659999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02089878}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776435671079,"responseId":"063174d5df90ade1257704aee21a1e8d"}}
