{"type":"message","id":"a9d46a62","parentId":"ece5f76d","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:18:43.140Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The protection context_protector.js doesn't call the gateway API. It's a standalone module that maintains its own message state and doesn't integrate with the gateway.\n\nLet me look at the actual approach: I should check if the ContextProtector (v8/src/context/) has a hook or event that's supposed to be triggered. And whether there's a hook in the gateway hooks system that could be used.Actually, let me take a step back. The real question is: what would a minimal but effective context management setup look like?\n\n1. **Token counting before each LLM call** - Hook into the pre-LLM-call event2. **If over threshold** - Call a summarization API to compress history3. **Update session with compressed history**4. \n\nThen continue with the LLM call. Looking at the gateway hooks available, the `message:preprocessed` hook fires before agent execution, which is exactly where I'd want to intercept and check token limits. I could create a hook that runs the ContextProtector at that point to compress history if needed before the LLM call proceeds.\n\nBut I'm realizing the protection module isn't actually integrated with the gateway at all. Let me reconsider this from the ground up. I should add context configuration to openclaw.json with token thresholds, verify the existing ContextProtector code, create a gateway hook that calls it, and potentially set up a compaction cron. Let me start by adding the context config and building out the hook.\n\nActually, I need to think about the proper architecture here. The gateway hooks operate asynchronously and shouldn't block the main message flow. The right approach is to configure context settings, have the gateway check context during assembly, and then handle truncation either through a lightweight internal method or an external API call.\n\nThe most practical path forward is to configure context thresholds in openclaw.json, verify what the gateway already supports, and create a hook that manages compaction if needed. Let me look at what the gateway context config actually does.","thinkingSignature":"7326f82fb0cc0ed9ee588ab45a039bd803ceafdea01da75460b70479b595a519"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jox0679l3346_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/v8/src/config.js 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97036,"output":438,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119112,"cost":{"input":0.0291108,"output":0.0005256,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03093468}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442710298,"responseId":"06319055fce84b8233a43afa1ea16f4b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"459d24b5","parentId":"a9d46a62","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:18:43.579Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jox0679l3346_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst yaml = require('yaml');\n\nfunction loadConfig() {\n  const env = process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development';\n  const defaultPath = path.join(__dirname, '../config/default.yaml');\n  const envPath = path.join(__dirname, `../config/${env}.yaml`);\n\n  const defaultConfig = yaml.parse(fs.readFileSync(defaultPath, 'utf8'));\n  let envConfig = {};\n  if (fs.existsSync(envPath)) {\n    envConfig = yaml.parse(fs.readFileSync(envPath, 'utf8'));\n  }\n\n  const config = deepMerge(defaultConfig, envConfig);\n\n  // 环境变量覆盖\n  if (process.env.PORT) config.server.port = parseInt(process.env.PORT);\n  if (process.env.DB_PATH) config.database.path = process.env.DB_PATH;\n  if (process.env.LOG_LEVEL) config.logging.level = process.env.LOG_LEVEL;\n\n  // 确保目录存在\n  ensureDir(path.dirname(config.database.path));\n  ensureDir(config.executor.workspaceRoot);\n  ensureDir(path.dirname(config.logging.file));\n\n  return config;\n}\n\nfunction deepMerge(target, source) {\n  for (const key in source) {\n    if (source[key] instanceof Object && key in target) {\n      Object.assign(source[key], deepMerge(target[key], source[key]));\n    }\n  }\n  return { ...target, ...source };\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { loadConfig };"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":239,"aggregated":"const fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst yaml = require('yaml');\n\nfunction loadConfig() {\n  const env = process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development';\n  const defaultPath = path.join(__dirname, '../config/default.yaml');\n  const envPath = path.join(__dirname, `../config/${env}.yaml`);\n\n  const defaultConfig = yaml.parse(fs.readFileSync(defaultPath, 'utf8'));\n  let envConfig = {};\n  if (fs.existsSync(envPath)) {\n    envConfig = yaml.parse(fs.readFileSync(envPath, 'utf8'));\n  }\n\n  const config = deepMerge(defaultConfig, envConfig);\n\n  // 环境变量覆盖\n  if (process.env.PORT) config.server.port = parseInt(process.env.PORT);\n  if (process.env.DB_PATH) config.database.path = process.env.DB_PATH;\n  if (process.env.LOG_LEVEL) config.logging.level = process.env.LOG_LEVEL;\n\n  // 确保目录存在\n  ensureDir(path.dirname(config.database.path));\n  ensureDir(config.executor.workspaceRoot);\n  ensureDir(path.dirname(config.logging.file));\n\n  return config;\n}\n\nfunction deepMerge(target, source) {\n  for (const key in source) {\n    if (source[key] instanceof Object && key in target) {\n      Object.assign(source[key], deepMerge(target[key], source[key]));\n    }\n  }\n  return { ...target, ...source };\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { loadConfig };","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776442723509}}
