{"type":"message","id":"15dca656","parentId":"e0dfee37","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:19:36.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the `compact` command doesn't seem to have a dedicated subcommand under the CLI. And the session context.json shows 0 messages - but that's because this is a new session or the context is stored differently.\n\nLet me now create the proper context management solution. Here's my plan:\n\n1. Configure `context` section in openclaw.json with sensible thresholds\n2. Create a hook that monitors context size and triggers compaction\n3. The compaction should use the existing summarization logic\n\nBut wait - looking at the actual gateway architecture, the `compact` command might just be a session-level command that the user can invoke.\n\nLet me think about what \"配置好\" actually means:\n\n\n- Configure context thresholds for alert/warning (when to trigger compaction)\n- Make the compaction work (compact session history)\n- Set up automatic triggering\n\nThe gateway has a `compaction.mode: safeguard` setting which likely enables automatic compaction. The SOUL.md mentions \"Compaction 压缩机制\" and \"自动记忆刷新\" where compaction triggers a silent turn before context is lost, prompting the AI to write important context to memory. So the real approach is configuring the context section with thresholds and enabling the safeguard mode to handle compaction automatically.\n\nI need to set up the context configuration in openclaw.json with token limits and alert thresholds, enable safeguard mode for compaction, and create a hook that monitors context size to trigger compaction when needed.","thinkingSignature":"38a6e6381775be051f8b2402812578d0ed04d1ac3c583ed668062c70c7e1eef4"},{"type":"text","text":"开始配置。先写入 context 段落到 openclaw.json：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qeih59reg197_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/openclaw.json","limit":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax"