{"type":"message","id":"876889fe","parentId":"5b180a3b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:20:10.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also check if the gateway will reload hooks automatically or if I need to restart it. Also, I should verify the hook will work by checking if the session context path is correct and readable.\n\nBut actually, the bigger issue is: the hook runs as a separate process. It needs to know:\n1. Which session to monitor\n2. Where the session context file is\n\nFor now, let me focus on making the gateway restart to pick up the config changes, and then verify the hook is registered.\n\nAlso, I should consider: instead of a custom hook, maybe I should use the built-in compaction mechanism. The gateway has a `compaction.mode: safeguard` setting. Maybe there's a way to trigger it.\n\nActually, let me also check what the `compact` CLI command does:","thinkingSignature":"211bc0a35327f9b0efbaa9dfc30df28e44d4cdfad006c0906d378a339a53fb9a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5pv4fmo32ezh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs help compact 2>&1 | head -10\n\necho \"\"\n# 检查 compact 相关的 gateway 命令\nnode ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs sessions --help 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101072,"output":263,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122973,"cost":{"input":0.030321599999999997,"output":0.0003156,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.031935479999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442803985,"responseId":"063190b15e5555309a35c7560f351b7c"}}
