{"type":"message","id":"019d0448","parentId":"78d8187d","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:21:35.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the cron is created. Now let me also restart the gateway to make sure everything is clean, and then verify the overall status.Actually, I should also make the session-summary hook work properly when session is compacted. The session-summary hook should run after /new and write a summary. If context gets compacted during the session, the summary at the end will capture the important stuff.\n\nLet me also think about what else needs to be done:1. ✅ context-monitor.js created\n2. ✅ context-monitor cron created (every 30 min)\n3. Need to: verify it works and test compaction4. \n\nThe session context path might be wrong for the current session since we're in webchat. I should double-check where the gateway actually stores the session context for webchat sessions. And I need to verify that the session-summary hook is properly configured with the session file path. Let me restart the gateway first to ensure the hook picks up the latest configuration.","thinkingSignature":"5abdf731f662fda3d7d2f5703e6a7b11fcc07839c21f6960c4153d79895aec3e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_86un3rlp76cz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user restart openclaw-gateway.service 2>&1\nsleep 4\nsystemctl --user status openclaw-gateway.service 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"Active|Main PID\" | head -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104485,"output":269,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126392,"cost":{"input":0.0313455,"output":0.0003228,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.032966579999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776442886260,"responseId":"06319104814e986dfc0a9119a97682a5"}}
