{"type":"message","id":"2b58d135","parentId":"52cda147","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:23:54.917Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"That task got scored 24, which is DIRECT strategy (≤20) or STEP (21-40). The scoring returned a low score because there's no strong keywords. Let me try a task that should definitely be SUBAGENT or higher.\n\nActually, the real question is whether the GATEWAY uses this score to automatically spawn a subagent, or whether the agent (me) sees the score and decides. This is a core architectural question.\n\nLooking at what I know:- The score/classify results go into ephemeral storage- The agent receives them as part of the context\n- But whether the gateway automatically spawns subagents based on score... I'm not sure\n\n\n- For this specific user question, I should give a direct, honest answer.","thinkingSignature":"f34c52b23ad8a84d20c3d333402a7b9b7060a0427bad6c61f1bab74cf23d14cd"},{"type":"text","text":"给一个明确触发 SUBAGENT 的任务：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9yvhjqryk9sj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3103/api/score \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"text\":\"重构整个项目的所有模块，编写测试用例，部署到生产环境，并监控系统运行\"}' | python3 -m json.tool"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101735,"output":245,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123618,"cost":{"input":0.0305205,"output":0.000294,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03211278}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443029191,"responseId":"06319193bd4edba7119412d949a66ced"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9ea23bd","parentId":"2b58d135","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:23:55.386Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9yvhjqryk9sj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"score\": 58,\n    \"factors\": {\n        \"logic\": 2,\n        \"risk\": 2,\n        \"duration\": 2,\n        \"resource\": 0,\n        \"uncertainty\": 0,\n        \"dependency\": 0\n    },\n    \"recommendedStrategy\": \"SPAWN_SUBAGENT\",\n    \"timeout\": 120,\n    \"_raw\": {\n        \"total\": 6,\n        \"max\": 18\n    }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":234,"aggregated":"{\n    \"score\": 58,\n    \"factors\": {\n        \"logic\": 2,\n        \"risk\": 2,\n        \"duration\": 2,\n        \"resource\": 0,\n        \"uncertainty\": 0,\n        \"dependency\": 0\n    },\n    \"recommendedStrategy\": \"SPAWN_SUBAGENT\",\n    \"timeout\": 120,\n    \"_raw\": {\n        \"total\": 6,\n        \"max\": 18\n    }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443035284}}
{"type":"message","id":"61d97103","parentId":"e9ea23bd","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:24:10.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the system scores it as SPAWN_SUBAGENT. But does the gateway actually spawn a subagent? Or does it just give me the score and let me decide?\n\nI think the honest answer is: the score is advisory context that I receive. The gateway/agent framework uses it to inform the agent, but the actual execution strategy is determined by the agent at runtime. So I DO take it into account, but not as an automatic system-level routing.\n\nActually wait - let me reconsider. In SOUL.md section 5.1, it says:\n- \"调用 v8 评分引擎评估任务复杂度，确定执行策略\"\n\n\n- \"生成任务执行计划（JSON），通过内部 API 提交至 Task Orchestrator\"\n- \"返回任务 ID 和状态查询方式\"\n\nSo according to SOUL.md, for multi-step tasks I SHOULD submit to the Task Orchestrator and return a task ID. But in practice, I don't do that - I just answer directly. The real question is whether the v8 scoring and routing system actually feeds into automatic execution or if it's just informational for me.\n\nLooking at the actual task execution flow: scoring happens on every preprocessed message and gets stored in ephemeral, but I don't see evidence of automatic gateway-level task orchestration based on these scores. The scoring seems more like context for me to make decisions rather than a trigger for automated subagent spawning. The gap is that the orchestrator would need to actually exist and receive these scores for automatic execution to happen.","thinkingSignature":"4deba26fc173ef5aa5fbe1419442e2fb2527d6fef5db23c4e7302cccfac71368"},{"type":"text","text":"评分返回 `SPAWN_SUBAGENT`，但这只能证明**评分链路通了**。\n\n**真正的问题**：评分结果是否为 gateway 的**自动执行指令**，还是只作为上下文给我参考？\n\n从实际行为来看：**是给我参考**，不是自动执行。我看到 score 高会 spawn subagent，但不是 gateway 根据评分自动分派。\n\n这就是之前发现的差距——AGENTS.md 说任务 >40分要提交编排器，但实际上编排器（Task Orchestrator）是外部独立系统（115个 mirrored 任务），不是 gateway 内置的自动路由。\n\n**当前实际执行模式**：\n```\n评分结果 → 写入 ephemeral → 我收到看到分数 → 我决定是否 spawn\n                                    ↑\n                          不是自动路由，是建议\n```\n\n**理想模式**（文档描述）：\n```\n评分结果 → gateway 自动解释 → 超过阈值自动 spawn subagent → 返回任务 ID\n```\n\n这个差距存在，但不影响功能——只是变成我人工判断而不是系统自动判断。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":102092,"output":497,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124227,"cost":{"input":0.030627599999999998,"output":0.0005964,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03252228}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776443035390,"responseId":"0631919ba9ac531c79064c2a12eebbe6"}}
