{"type":"message","id":"1361969d","parentId":"1dc002ad","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:25:07.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know how to make the system automatically route based on the score, rather than relying on me (the AI) to read the score and manually decide.\n\nLooking at the architecture, there are a few approaches:\n\n1. **The auto-score-classify hook** already intercepts messages and calls v8 scorer/classifier before I receive them. The results are written to ephemeral. But the hook doesn't take automatic action based on the score.\n\n2. **A custom middleware/action hook** that, after scoring, if score > threshold, automatically spawns a subagent using `sessions_spawn` tool.\n\n3. **Modify the gateway's agent orchestration** to automatically spawn subagents based on score.\n   \nThe most practical approach would be a hook that detects when the score exceeds a threshold and uses the `sessions_spawn` tool to create a subagent automatically. Since I can't see the actual implementation details of how the auto-score-classify hook works or what context it's writing to ephemeral, I'll focus on building a custom hook that reads those results and triggers the subagent spawning when needed.\n\nBut there's a fundamental constraint here—the subagent spawning needs to happen before the main agent starts processing, and once a response begins, it's too late. So I'd need a pre-processing hook that evaluates the score and decides whether to spawn first.\n\nThe most practical approach is creating a custom hook that checks the score in ephemeral right after auto-score-classify runs, and if it's above a certain threshold, uses `agent:preparing` to spawn a subagent before the main agent even starts. Alternatively, if OpenClaw has built-in config like `agents.defaults.maxConcurrent` or routing rules, that could handle the automatic decision without custom code. I need to figure out where in the message processing flow the score gets used to determine the right interception point.","thinkingSignature":"f370367044d1b8d73d781618adbbb4cefbd0960de36d1d0411ddfcfb2296f1fa"},{"type":"text","text":"`agent:preparing` 事件触发后，根据评分自动 fork：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g0fa9b3juwka_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":435,"cacheRead":122642,"cacheWrite":895,"totalTokens":124030,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.000522,"cacheRead":0.0073585199999999995,"cacheWrite":0.000335625,"total":0.008233544999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443091404,"responseId":"063191d37362411ae0e79dab19ebfb0c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"202d8448","parentId":"1361969d","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:25:08.237Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g0fa9b3juwka_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3105) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n// + ephemeral memory capture for meaningful messages\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = ["}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":244,"aggregated":"// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3105) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n// + ephemeral memory capture for meaningful messages\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = [","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443108155}}
{"type":"message","id":"67617212","parentId":"202d8448","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:25:18.137Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the auto-score-classify hook already does classification and scoring, and writes results to ephemeral. But it doesn't take automatic routing action.\n\nThe key question is: does the gateway read the ephemeral file and use the score to automatically route? Or does it just pass the score as context to me?\n\nLet me check if there's a gateway-level routing based on ephemeral data.\n\nActually, looking at the SOUL.md section 5.1:\n\"需要多步骤执行时 → 调用 v8 评分 → 提交编排器 → 返回任务 ID\"\n\nThis says \"需要调用\" - meaning the agent (me) calls the orchestrator. \n\nThe distinction is becoming clearer: when a task requires multiple steps, I'm the one who invokes the v8 scorer, and based on that score, I decide whether to submit to the orchestrator. The system doesn't automatically route based on the score - it's a manual decision point where I evaluate whether the complexity warrants escalation. So the automatic routing isn't really happening at all. The agent reads the score from ephemeral and decides whether to spawn a subagent based on that information.\n\nI could create a hook that intercepts before the agent processes a message and automatically spawns a subagent if the score exceeds a threshold, essentially acting as a pre-agent router. This would route to a subagent session, but the question is whether the main agent then waits for that subagent to complete or if the subagent handles the response independently.","thinkingSignature":"2eeea2fe035ffcaff6c24183255383bf0e635d0e00176753dbaa7376d70f8a7f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kx4gsiy1undd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"preagent\\|pre.agent\\|agent:preparing\\|event.*preparing\" ~/.openclaw/v8/src/ --include=\"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".js.map\" | head -10\n\necho \"---\"\ncat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null | grep -A5 \"events\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":102781,"output":401,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124820,"cost":{"input":0.0308343,"output":0.0004812,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.032613779999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443108241,"responseId":"063191e2f867569f5d281646dc34a8fd"}}
