{"type":"message","id":"2ed188c9","parentId":"1f07313f","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:00.876Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No built-in routing rules for automatic subagent spawning based on score. The gateway config doesn't have this.\n\nThe real solution is to create a custom pre-agent hook that:1. Fires on `agent:preparing` event\n2. Reads the score from ephemeral (set by auto-score-classify)3. If score > 40, calls the gateway API to spawn a subagent\n4. The subagent handles the task, main agent waits or returns a \"任务已提交\" messageBut I need to find out how to call the gateway from a hook to spawn a subagent. The ACP protocol has a way to talk to the gateway from outside.Let me look at how the ACP bridge works and whether it can spawn agents.Actually, the cleanest approach I can build right now:A `agent:preparing` hook that:\n1. Reads ephemeral for the score\n\n\n2. If score >= 50, spawns a subagent using `openclaw agent` CLI with the same message\n\nBut here's the timing issue - if the hook spawns a subagent, does the main agent still run? Looking at the SOUL.md spec, the flow is: user message → auto-score-classify hook fires → results written to ephemeral → `agent:preparing` event fires → I receive message + score context → if score high, I spawn subagent. But I want automatic spawning, not manual.\n\nThe practical path forward is building a hook that runs in the pre-agent phase to read the score and conditionally trigger a subagent spawn before the main agent starts. The `agent:preparing` event would be ideal, but I need to verify it actually exists. If it doesn't, `message:preprocessed` could work since auto-score-classify runs there first. Let me create a new hook that fires after auto-score-classify to read the score and spawn the subagent automatically.\n\nSince I can't directly call `sessions_spawn` from a hook, I'll use `agent:preparing` to read the score from ephemeral, and if it's high enough, spawn a subagent using `nohup openclaw agent` to run detached before returning control.","thinkingSignature":"b9fef97b30294dddf1f776693c519bd69ece101030041df96fc1bc53cb8b7f5d"},{"type":"text","text":"核心问题：没有内置的自动路由。需要自己接。\n\n**方案**：`agent:preparing` 事件触发时，检查 ephemeral 分数，超过阈值自动 fork 子 agent：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ue0h41lsc2us_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-router/HOOK.md","content":"name: auto-router\ndescription: \"读取 ephemeral 中的 v8 评分结果，超过阈值时自动 fork 子 agent 处理，主 agent 返回任务已提交。\"\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"🔀\",\n      \"events\": [\"agent:preparing\"],\n      \"requires\": {\"bins\": [\"node\"], \"config\": []},\n      \"always\": true\n    }\n  }\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104277,"output":610,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126525,"cost":{"input":0.0312831,"output":0.000732,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033313380000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443143238,"responseId":"06319207686548abe6d8a94658e7372d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b76f4132","parentId":"2ed188c9","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:01.386Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ue0h41lsc2us_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 271 bytes to /home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-router/HOOK.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443161300}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c493a84","parentId":"b76f4132","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:10.883Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I need to think about this more carefully. The `agent:preparing` event - does it actually exist? Looking at the auto-score-classify hook, it fires on `message:preprocessed`. There's no `agent:preparing` event documented in the available hooks.\n\nActually, let me think about the flow differently. What if the auto-score-classify hook, after writing the score, also checks the score and spawns the subagent? The hook fires on `message:preprocessed`, after classification and scoring. If the hook determines the score is high, it could spawn a subagent to handle the task.\n\nBut the issue is: if the hook spawns a subagent and the task gets handled, the main agent still receives the message and responds. We'd get two responses.\n \nI think the better approach is to have the hook detect a high score and send the message to a subagent instead, with the main agent returning something like \"任务已提交到子agent处理\" to avoid duplicate responses. I need to verify whether `agent:preparing` is actually a supported event type in OpenClaw though, since that affects whether this approach is even viable.","thinkingSignature":"15d15048d8116ac4a94d49fd45de1fbbf8af58d2dae4582121ae79b771b13787"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dij01izfdrck_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"agent:preparing\\|agent:start\\|agent:before\" ~/.openclaw/v8/src/ --include=\"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".js.map\" | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# Check what events are actually supported by looking at event registrations\ngrep -r \"emit\\|on(\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/ --include=\"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104925,"output":364,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126927,"cost":{"input":0.0314775,"output":0.0004368,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03321258}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443161390,"responseId":"06319217150cd2f583abcce1125cbe0c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"238cd8c2","parentId":"6c493a84","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:11.366Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dij01izfdrck_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:async function runClassification(text) {\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:    runClassification(text),"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":228,"aggregated":"---\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:async function runClassification(text) {\n/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js:    runClassification(text),","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443171267}}
{"type":"message","id":"3de9ddd6","parentId":"238cd8c2","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:37.531Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`agent:preparing` doesn't seem to exist as a real event in the gateway source. The auto-score-classify hook fires on `message:preprocessed`, which is the only event I can reliably use.\n\nLet me think about the cleanest approach:\n\nSince the hook fires on `message:preprocessed`, I could modify the auto-score-classify hook to also handle spawning. But that's modifying existing behavior.\n\nThe best approach:\n1. Create a new hook that fires on `message:preprocessed` (after auto-score-classify)\n2. It reads the ephemeral file that auto-score-classify wrote\n3. It checks if score > threshold\n\n\n4. If so, spawns a subagent using `sessions_spawn` tool - but hooks can't use tools directly, only the agent can\n5. Actually, hooks run as separate processes and could call the gateway via WebSocket or HTTP, but that's complex\n6. The simplest solution: have the hook write a signal file, then use a cron every minute to check for signals and spawn subagents - but that's too slow\n\nI need to think about this differently. Looking at the task orchestrator v3 skill, it says I should call the v8 scorer when a task needs multiple steps and submit to the task orchestrator, which returns a task ID. But that's what I'm supposed to do as the agent - the question is whether the system automatically does this. The SOUL.md decision tree says I should call the v8 scorer for multi-step tasks and generate an execution plan via the internal API, submitting it to the Task Orchestrator.\n\nThe gap is: I might not actually be doing this automatically - I'm supposed to call the scorer myself when I detect a multi-step task, then submit to the orchestrator. But the scoring already happens via the auto-score-classify hook before I even see the message. So I receive the message with the score already calculated. The question is whether I'm actually using that score to decide to spawn a subagent, or whether I'm just answering directly.\n\nThe auto-router hook needs to intercept at `agent:preparing` - but that event might not actually exist. The most reliable approach would be to modify the auto-score-classify hook to also handle spawning when the score exceeds a threshold, using the ACP protocol's `agent` command to spawn a subagent session. The hook would send a message to the agent to handle the task, and the main agent returns \"NO_REPLY\" to signal it shouldn't respond.","thinkingSignature":"ccdacb019fb18edc7775e1a629038785f394dc0d6bca2991f901b54f236fe038"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8cqxlzidx6k7_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/scripts/auto-router.js","content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Auto-Router Hook\n * 监听 agent:preparing 事件，检查评分，超阈值自动 fork 子 agent\n * \n * 触发时机：auto-score-classify 写入 ephemeral 之后\n * 阈值：score >= 40 → SPAWN_SUBAGENT\n */\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { spawn } = require('child_process');\n\nconst EPHEMERAL_DIR = '/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral';\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst GW_URL = 'http://127.0.0.1:18789';\nconst GW_TOKEN = '5e7ab299281fb2ffbdbb922f9939d9abbe5e15321f6cb901';\n\n// 找最新的 ephemeral\nfunction getLatestEphemeral() {\n  const files = fs.readdirSync(EPHEMERAL_DIR)\n    .filter(f => f.endsWith('.jsonl') && f.startsWith('2026'))\n    .map(f => ({\n      name: f,\n      mtime: fs.statSync(path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, f)).mtime\n    }))\n    .sort((a, b) => b.mtime - a.mtime);\n  return files[0]?.name;\n}\n\n// 读最新 ephemeral 最后一行\nfunction getLatestScore() {\n  const latest = getLatestEphemeral();\n  if (!latest) return null;\n  \n  const lines = fs.readFileSync(path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, latest), 'utf8')\n    .trim().split('\\n');\n  \n  for (let i = lines.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n    try {\n      const entry = JSON.parse(lines[i]);\n      if (entry.score !== undefined) {\n        return entry.score;\n      }\n    } catch {}\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\n// 通过 ACP 协议 spawn 子 agent\nfunction spawnSubagent(message, score) {\n  const args = [\n    '/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/node',\n    '/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs',\n    'agent',\n    '--session', `agent:main:subagent:${Date.now()}`,\n    '--message', message,\n    '--score', String(score),\n    '--deliver'\n  ];\n  \n  const proc = spawn(args[0], args.slice(1), {\n    detached: true,\n    stdio: 'ignore'\n  });\n  proc.unref();\n  console.log(`[auto-router] Spawned subagent for score=${score}`);\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const event = process.env.OPENCLAW_EVENT || '';\n  \n  // 等待 auto-score-classify 完成\n  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));\n  \n  const score = getLatestScore();\n  if (score === null) {\n    console.log('[auto-router] No score found');\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  console.log(`[auto-router] Latest score: ${score}`);\n  \n  if (score >= SCORE_THRESHOLD) {\n    const message = process.env.OPENCLAW_MESSAGE || '';\n    if (message) {\n      spawnSubagent(message, score);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nmain().catch(console.error);\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":105441,"output":1256,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128335,"cost":{"input":0.031632299999999995,"output":0.0015072,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.034437779999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443171371,"responseId":"063192234daa2c823ca5c2418752d9d6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"47441668","parentId":"3de9ddd6","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:37.934Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8cqxlzidx6k7_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 2330 bytes to /home/ai/.openclaw/scripts/auto-router.js"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443197865}}
{"type":"message","id":"3969235d","parentId":"47441668","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:52.295Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, I'm overcomplicating this. Let me think about the real practical approach.\n\nThe ACP protocol can spawn agents. The `openclaw agent` command can run a single agent turn. But there's a cleaner way - using the `sessions_spawn` tool within a hook is not possible, but I can have the hook trigger a background process that sends a message to the gateway.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The simplest approach:\n\n1. **The gateway's `agent` command** can be used to spawn a session: `openclaw agent --message \"xxx\" --session agent:main:subagent:xxx`\n2. The hook fires on `message:preprocessed`\n\n\n3. If score is high, it reads the message from the ephemeral file, spawns a detached `openclaw agent` subprocess with the message, and the main agent returns NO_REPLY\n\nBut there's a timing issue - the auto-score-classify hook fires synchronously on `message:preprocessed` before the agent processes the message. If my hook also fires on the same event and spawns a subagent synchronously, both would run. I need to rethink this so the auto-router hook fires after auto-score-classify, checks if the score is high, and spawns the subagent if needed.\n\nThe simplest approach is to have auto-router fire on `message:preprocessed` (after auto-score-classify), read the latest ephemeral score, and if score >= 40, spawn a subagent via detached `openclaw agent` subprocess before returning. This way the hook runs before the agent and spawns the subagent without waiting for it to complete.\n\nI'm checking if there's a way to suppress the main agent response when a subagent handles the task, but I don't see a clear mechanism. So the practical solution is: if the score is high, spawn the subagent and let it handle the task while the main agent continues normally. The user would see both responses, but that's acceptable for now.","thinkingSignature":"3199f784752c93617e83115bdb94664ff428469059a1b7dac62eca790d14b4cd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_buerq0km5xg2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"chmod +x /home/ai/.openclaw/scripts/auto-router.js\n\n# 先测试：检查当前 ephemeral 最新的 score\nnode /home/ai/.openclaw/scripts/auto-router.js 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106732,"output":474,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128844,"cost":{"input":0.032019599999999995,"output":0.0005688,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033886679999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443197938,"responseId":"0631923dd67f82cc1b057560d8b65f78"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b83ccd43","parentId":"3969235d","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:26:52.523Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_buerq0km5xg2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"exec\",\n  \"error\": \"exec preflight: complex interpreter invocation detected; refusing to run without script preflight validation. Use a direct `python <file>.py` or `node <file>.js` command.\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"exec","error":"exec preflight: complex interpreter invocation detected; refusing to run without script preflight validation. Use a direct `python <file>.py` or `node <file>.js` command."},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443212453}}
{"type":"message","id":"281dfe1b","parentId":"b83ccd43","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:27:08.045Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The exec preflight is blocking again. Let me use a simpler approach - just write the hook handler directly as a simple script that can be called by the gateway.\n\nActually, looking at this problem again, I think the simplest reliable approach is:1. Don't try to suppress the main agent\n2. Let both the main agent and subagent respond3. This gives the user two responses - one quick assessment from main, one detailed from subagent\n\nBut wait, there's a better approach. Let me look at how the `sessions_spawn` tool works. The tool is available to ME (the agent) during my turn. So what if:\n1. I receive a message with score = 582. I decide (automatically, not manually) to spawn a subagent\n3. \n\nI use `sessions_spawn` to create a subagent, then return NO_REPLY so only the subagent responds. The real question is whether the system automatically invokes `sessions_spawn` when I see a high score, or if I need to manually call it. Looking at SOUL.md section 5.1, the pattern is clear: when a task requires multi-step execution, I should call the v8 scorer to get a score, submit to the task orchestrator, and return the task ID to the user rather than executing it myself.\n\nBut here's the issue—I'm receiving the score from the hook now, so the question becomes whether I actually follow through with spawning. The auto-router hook should intercept before I even see the message, check if the score is high enough, and automatically spawn a subagent to handle it instead of me responding directly.\n\nHowever, there's a practical problem: I can't return NO_REPLY from a hook since hooks don't send responses. So the auto-router would spawn the subagent, but the main agent would still process and respond anyway, creating duplicate responses. The real solution requires either a pre-agent hook that suppresses the main agent, or automatic spawning that waits for the subagent to complete before the main agent responds. Since the gateway controls agent execution and hooks run in sequence, the hook approach might actually work if I set it up correctly.\n\nLet me reconsider: the auto-score-classify hook fires first and writes the score, then auto-router fires on the same event and spawns the subagent. The key is that if auto-router spawns a detached subagent and exits immediately, the gateway then runs the main agent afterward. But both would respond to the user, which is wrong. I think the simpler solution is to not override auto-score-classify at all—just accept that I handle routing myself when I see a high score, and document this for the user so they understand that's how it works.","thinkingSignature":"08c5b01cf3f036382239fcdb6b434098b3056d9e7b5152229994a556bde37441"},{"type":"text","text":"auto-score-classify 已经写入评分了，但无法拦截主 agent。我来改 auto-score-classify 本身，加上自动 spawn 逻辑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hmfd40t9jn9s_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107279,"output":622,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129539,"cost":{"input":0.032183699999999996,"output":0.0007463999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.034228379999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443212526,"responseId":"0631924be94d14aa36a9b8989ffeafda"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d38f5bc4","parentId":"281dfe1b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:27:08.499Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hmfd40t9jn9s_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// auto-score-classify hook\n// Concurrent classification (3105) + scoring (3103) on every inbound message\n// + ephemeral memory capture for meaningful messages\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 3000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 3000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 3000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = [\n  /记住|以后都|决定用|别用|改用|这个要记|记下来/,\n];\n\nfunction isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring) {\n  const c = classification || {};\n  const s = scoring || {};\n\n  // 1. Explicit user intent (highest priority)\n  if (MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS.some(p => p.test(text))) return true;\n\n  // 2. System-level important\n  if (c.intercepted === true) return true;\n  if (c.scene === 'fault_recovery') return true;\n\n  // 3. High risk or MEGA task\n  if ((s.factors?.risk || 0) >= 3) return true;\n  if (s.recommendedStrategy === 'MEGA_TASK') return true;\n\n  // 4. Substantial content (非只言片语)\n  if (text.trim().length > 80) return true;\n\n  return false;\n}\n\n// ─── Ephemeral memory writer ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst EPHEMERAL_DIR = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\",\n  \"ephemeral\"\n);\n\nfunction writeEphemeral(entry) {\n  try {\n    ensureDir(EPHEMERAL_DIR);\n    // File per hour: YYYY-MM-DD-HH.jsonl\n    const now = new Date();\n    const hourStr = now.toISOString().slice(0, 13).replace('T', '-');\n    const filePath = path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, `${hourStr}.jsonl`);\n    const line = JSON.stringify(entry) + '\\n';\n    fs.appendFileSync(filePath, line, 'utf-8');\n  } catch (e) {\n    // Silently ignore write errors - ephemeral should not break main flow\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Main handler ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classificationResult, scoringResult] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const classification = classificationResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classificationResult.value : null;\n  const scoring = scoringResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoringResult.value : null;\n\n  const result = {\n    classification,\n    scoring,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n  };\n\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    // ignore write errors silently\n  }\n\n  // ─── Ephemeral memory capture ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n  if (isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring)) {\n    writeEphemeral({\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      sessionKey,\n      text,\n      textPreview: text.length > 200 ? text.slice(0, 200) + '...' : text,\n      classification,\n      scoring,\n    });\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443228388}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3ba4647","parentId":"d38f5bc4","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:27:20.380Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full auto-score-classify handler. It writes the result to `context.json` in the session directory, and also writes to ephemeral if the message is \"meaningful\".\n\nThe `result` object (with `classification` and `scoring`) is written to `context.json`. This is what I (the agent) read as context.\n\nTo add auto-routing, I need to:\n1. After getting the score, if score >= 40, spawn a subagent\n2. The subagent handles the task\n3. The main agent should return NO_REPLY\n\nThe problem: the hook can't return NO_REPLY. The hook just runs code.\n \nWait, I'm seeing the real issue now. The hook itself can't suppress the agent response—there's no mechanism for that. But I could write the score to context.json and let the agent decide what to do. The actual implementation would be: when the score is high enough, spawn a subagent to handle it, and have the main agent return NO_REPLY so only the subagent responds.\n\nThe cleanest path forward is to keep the existing flow where I get the message with the score already calculated, then decide whether to spawn a subagent myself based on that score. I won't add complexity to the hook. The auto-router.js script I wrote might be useful later for scheduled checking, but for now the manual approach is sufficient.\n\nActually, thinking about this more—the gateway is the one orchestrating everything. If the hook could communicate directly with it through a Unix socket or HTTP to say \"don't run the agent, spawn a subagent instead,\" that would solve it. There's already an exec-approvals.sock for approvals, so maybe there's a similar mechanism for agent spawning I haven't found yet.","thinkingSignature":"d38fd2efdc6534be0700048c29ded153f761fc024f7c2377b9b5996ad1e4d8d6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6uddfa5zs71h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/*.sock ~/.openclaw/*.sock.* 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\nls /home/ai/.openclaw/agents/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109037,"output":424,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131099,"cost":{"input":0.0327111,"output":0.0005088,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.034518179999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443228506,"responseId":"0631925c80d058bfe4587cda1ae39ad2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b801ff8","parentId":"e3ba4647","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:27:20.936Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6uddfa5zs71h_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ncoder\ncodex\ndeep\ndeep_agent\nfast\nfast_agent\nmain\nthinker"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":250,"aggregated":"---\ncoder\ncodex\ndeep\ndeep_agent\nfast\nfast_agent\nmain\nthinker","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776443240824}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b43037e","parentId":"8b801ff8","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:27:48.137Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No Unix sockets visible. Let me think about this differently.\n\nActually, let me look at the ACP protocol. The ACP is the Agent Control Protocol. It might have a way to control agent spawning.\n\nActually, you know what? I've been spending too much time on this. Let me step back and give the user a practical answer.\n\nThe fundamental issue: OpenClaw doesn't have a built-in \"auto-route to subagent based on score\" feature. This would need to be implemented at the gateway level or through a custom middleware.\n\nThe cleanest approach I can actually implement:\n1. Modify auto-score-classify hook to spawn a subagent when score >= 40\n\n\n2. Spawn it as a detached process with the message text\n3. Write a marker to the session context file\n4. Have the main agent check for this marker and return NO_REPLY if found\n\nThis way the hook can actually trigger the subagent spawning, and the main agent will suppress itself when it sees the marker. Let me implement this approach by modifying the auto-score-classify hook.","thinkingSignature":"6ee9ca912bcef77d04748ab4af362e51a1585ec711de6742bf0252336c334265"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。auto-score-classify 的 context.json 会写入评分结果。主 agent 读取 context.json 时可以自动判断是否 spawn。\n\n但更彻底的方案：**修改 auto-score-classify hook，加上自动 fork**。让 hook 直接 spawn 子 agent，主 agent 只在没触发 fork 时才响应：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bvuv51opp5oy_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js","content":"// auto-score-classify hook v2\n// + 自动 fork 子 agent（score >= 40）\n// + 主 agent 标记文件（agent 检查后决定是否 NO_REPLY）\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport http from \"node:http\";\nimport { spawn } from \"node:child_process\";\n\nconst GW_TOKEN = '5e7ab299281fb2ffbdbb922f9939d9abbe5e15321f6cb901';\nconst SCORE_THRESHOLD = 40;\nconst AUTO_SPAWN_THRESHOLD = 50;\n\nasync function fetchJSON(url, body, timeoutMs = 4000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify(body);\n    const req = http.request(\n      url,\n      {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"Content-Length\": Buffer.byteLength(postData) },\n      },\n      (res) => {\n        let data = \"\";\n        res.on(\"data\", (chunk) => (data += chunk));\n        res.on(\"end\", () => {\n          try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); }\n          catch { resolve(null); }\n        });\n      }\n    );\n    req.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n    req.setTimeout(timeoutMs, () => { req.destroy(); resolve(null); });\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n    setTimeout(() => { try { req.destroy(); } catch {} }, timeoutMs);\n  });\n}\n\nasync function runClassification(text) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3105/classify\", { text }, 4000);\n}\n\nasync function runScoring(prompt) {\n  return fetchJSON(\"http://127.0.0.1:3103/api/score\", { prompt }, 4000);\n}\n\nfunction ensureDir(dir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Meaningfulness filter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS = [\n  /记住|以后都|决定用|别用|改用|这个要记|记下来/,\n];\n\nfunction isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring) {\n  const c = classification || {};\n  const s = scoring || {};\n  if (MEANINGFUL_PATTERNS.some(p => p.test(text))) return true;\n  if (c.intercepted === true) return true;\n  if (c.scene === 'fault_recovery') return true;\n  if ((s.factors?.risk || 0) >= 3) return true;\n  if (s.recommendedStrategy === 'MEGA_TASK') return true;\n  if (text.trim().length > 80) return true;\n  return false;\n}\n\n// ─── Ephemeral writer ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst EPHEMERAL_DIR = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\",\n  \"ephemeral\"\n);\n\nfunction writeEphemeral(entry) {\n  try {\n    ensureDir(EPHEMERAL_DIR);\n    const now = new Date();\n    const hourStr = now.toISOString().slice(0, 13).replace('T', '-');\n    const filePath = path.join(EPHEMERAL_DIR, `${hourStr}.jsonl`);\n    fs.appendFileSync(filePath, JSON.stringify(entry) + '\\n', 'utf-8');\n  } catch {}\n}\n\n// ─── Auto-spawn subagent ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction autoSpawn(message, sessionKey, scoring) {\n  const openclawPath = '/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/openclaw.mjs';\n  const subSessionKey = `agent:main:subagent:${Date.now()}`;\n  \n  const markerPath = `/tmp/openclaw-subagent-marker-${process.pid}`;\n  fs.writeFileSync(markerPath, JSON.stringify({\n    subSessionKey,\n    parentSession: sessionKey,\n    score: scoring?.score,\n    strategy: scoring?.recommendedStrategy,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n  }), 'utf-8');\n  \n  // Spawn detached - runs independently\n  spawn(\n    'node',\n    [openclawPath, 'agent', '--session', subSessionKey, '--message', message, '--score', String(scoring?.score || 0)],\n    {\n      detached: true,\n      stdio: 'ignore',\n      cwd: process.env.HOME || '/home/ai'\n    }\n  ).unref();\n  \n  // Write marker to session dir so main agent knows to return NO_REPLY\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  try {\n    const markerFile = path.join(sessionDir, '.subagent-triggered');\n    fs.writeFileSync(markerFile, subSessionKey, 'utf-8');\n  } catch {}\n  \n  console.log(`[auto-score-classify] Spawned subagent session=${subSessionKey} score=${scoring?.score}`);\n}\n\n// ─── Main handler ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nexport default async function handler(event) {\n  if (event.type !== \"message\" || event.action !== \"preprocessed\") {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const text = event.context?.bodyForAgent || \"\";\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) return;\n\n  const sessionKey = event.sessionKey || \"default\";\n  const sessionDir = path.join(process.env.HOME || \"/home/ai\", \".openclaw/sessions\", sessionKey);\n  ensureDir(sessionDir);\n\n  const [classificationResult, scoringResult] = await Promise.allSettled([\n    runClassification(text),\n    runScoring(text),\n  ]);\n\n  const classification = classificationResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? classificationResult.value : null;\n  const scoring = scoringResult.status === \"fulfilled\" ? scoringResult.value : null;\n  const score = scoring?.score ?? 0;\n\n  const result = {\n    classification,\n    scoring,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    messagePreview: text.slice(0, 120),\n    _autoSpawned: score >= AUTO_SPAWN_THRESHOLD,\n  };\n\n  // Write context.json (main agent reads this)\n  const outPath = path.join(sessionDir, \"context.json\");\n  try {\n    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {}\n\n  // Auto-spawn if score >= AUTO_SPAWN_THRESHOLD\n  if (score >= AUTO_SPAWN_THRESHOLD) {\n    autoSpawn(text, sessionKey, scoring);\n  }\n\n  // Ephemeral memory\n  if (isMeaningful(text, classification, scoring)) {\n    writeEphemeral({\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      sessionKey,\n      text,\n      textPreview: text.length > 200 ? text.slice(0, 200) + '...' : text,\n      classification,\n      scoring,\n    });\n  }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109497,"output":1834,"cacheRead":21638,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132969,"cost":{"input":0.0328491,"output":0.0022007999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00129828,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03634818}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776443240939,"responseId":"06319267ea03be3c745bc64d5686533d"}}
