{"type":"message","id":"4526cba4","parentId":"e453411a","timestamp":"2026-04-17T16:48:14.938Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants the agent to autonomously call sessions_spawn when it sees the instruction. This is fundamentally about agent behavior - can we make an agent \"see\" an instruction in its context and then autonomously call a tool?\n\nThe answer is: **only if the instruction is in the system prompt or if there's a skill that matches the description and triggers automatically**.\n\nFrom SOUL.md's Skills section:\n> 当用户消息匹配 skill 的 `description` 时：读取对应 `SKILL.md`，按其中指令执行\n\nSo skills are triggered by USER MESSAGE matching the skill's description. But the instruction is injected by the hook into bodyForAgent - not as a user message, but as the modified prompt that the agent receives.\n \nThe hook is modifying the prompt itself, not the user message. The distinction matters because when bodyForAgent gets modified to \"请调用 sessions_spawn...\", the model receives it as part of the prompt it should respond to, not as a user message that would trigger a skill. So the real question becomes: will the model actually call sessions_spawn just because we tell it to in the prompt, or does it need something more explicit like a tool call format?\n\nMy honest answer is that this approach has almost no chance of working. The model would need to recognize that it should use sessions_spawn, but the only reliable way to make it do so is through a skill or system prompt instruction - not through an injected prompt modification. Even then, skills only trigger on user messages, so I can't inject a skill trigger through bodyForAgent. I'm at an impasse where the user's request to make the agent autonomously call sessions_spawn based on my instructions can't be reliably achieved with the current architecture.","thinkingSignature":"067b8ea29ed5c271603da5f6b1c12a117200561a463700e2133226e391ea0c04"},{"type":"text","text":"<thinking>\n### 1. 需求拆解\n用户要的是：Agent 看到指令后\"自主\"调用 sessions_spawn，不需要人介入。\n\n### 2. 核心矛盾\n\n\"自主\"的定义：\n- **Agent 视角**：根据输入自己决定是否调用工具\n- **用户视角**：人不用说什么，Agent 自动去做\n\n但 Agent 的行为完全由 prompt 控制。\"自主调用\"的前提是：prompt 里明确告诉它\"遇到 X 就做 Y\"。\n\n### 3. 唯一的\"自主\"路径\n\n根据 SOUL.md 的 Skills 机制：\n> 当用户消息**匹配** skill 的 `description` 时 → 读取 SKILL.md → 按指令执行\n\n所以如果用户消息里包含特定关键词，就触发 skill，skill 里告诉它调用 sessions_spawn。\n\n但这需要**用户消息本身**包含触发词，不是 hook 注入的文本。\n\n### 4. Hook 注入 vs Skill 触发的根本区别\n\n| | Hook 注入 | Skill 触发 |\n|--|---------|-----------|\n| 时机 | 消息已被修改 | 用户消息到达时 |\n| 对象 | bodyForAgent（agent 的输入） | user message（原始） |\n| 可靠性 | 靠模型\"听话\" | 靠描述匹配 |\n| 自主性 | 无可靠自主 | 相对可靠 |\n\n### 5. 真正的问题\n\n用户要的是\"hook 注入 → Agent 自主调用\"。这要求模型在收到非标准格式的指令时，**自发地**选择调用工具而不是生成文本。\n\n这是不可能的。唯一\"自主\"的方式是 skill 机制，但 skill 匹配的是用户消息，不是 hook 注入的文本。\n\n### 6. 最终结论\n\n没有可靠的方式让 Agent\"自主\"调用 sessions_spawn。唯一的可行路径需要用户在消息里包含特定触发词，然后通过 skill 触发。但这改变了用户行为，不符合\"自动化\"的要求。\n\n这是当前架构下的物理限制，不是努力能解决的问题。\n</thinking>\n\n---\n\n**\"自主\"在 Agent 系统里是有前提的**。\n\nAgent 的\"自主\"只来自两种机制：\n\n1. **System prompt 明确告诉它**：\"遇到 X 就做 Y\"\n2. **Skill description 匹配用户消息** → 自动加载 skill 指令\n\n没有第三种方式能让 Agent\"看到一段文字就自主行动\"。\n\n---\n\n**你的需求**：`hook 注入 → Agent 看到指令 → 自主调用 sessions_spawn`\n\n这不存在可靠的实现路径，除非：\n- 用户消息本身包含触发词（如\"派发\"、\"spawn\"）\n- Skill 的 description 匹配这个触发词\n- Skill 指令里明确告诉 Agent 调用 sessions_spawn\n\n但这已经改变了用户行为，不叫自动化派发了。\n\n---\n\n**诚实的结论**：这不是实现细节问题，是\"让 Agent 自主响应 hook 注入的文本\"本身在当前架构下不成立。Agent 不会无中生有地调用工具，只能响应明确的指令或匹配到的 skill。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":956,"cacheRead":139466,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":140422,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0.0011472,"cacheRead":0.008367959999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009515159999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776444464057,"responseId":"0631972eaa9e778b8c5aeb82645ae98a"}}
